## Issue

I have the following error when running solidity test with truffle: 
`Error: Callback was already called.`
I found something similar on the internet here: https://ethereum.stackexchange.com/questions/69406/callback-was-already-called-during-truffle-test-using-a-solidity-testfile

## Steps to Reproduce

When running on the development network `truffle test` of the following contract:
```javascript
pragma solidity ^0.5.10;

import "truffle/Assert.sol";

contract TestUnpackFixed {

  function testUnpackFixed() public {
    uint expectedLength = 1;
    uint a = 1;
    Assert.equal(
      a,
      expectedLength,
      "unpack array length should equal expectedLength");
  }
}
```
truffle-config.js
```javascript
module.exports = {
  networks: {
    development: {
      host: '127.0.0.1',
      port: 7545,
      network_id: '47',
      gas: 4700000,
      gasPrice: 6000000000,
    },
  },

  mocha: {
    reporter: 'eth-gas-reporter',
  },

  compilers: {
    solc: {
      version: '0.5.10',
      settings: {
        optimizer: {
          enabled: true,
          runs: 200,
        },
      },
    },
  },
}
```

